parameters:
...My apologies for the late introduction. My name is
\C[2]Yuri Orlov\C[0]. Please remember me.

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[2]Oh, hello, I'm Amagawa Kohane. I'm the magical girl
Seraphiel.

I've heard rumors about you. The rising star of the
Guardians, they say...

If you don't mind, would you like to take a look at the
products I offer? I'm sure they can be of use to you.

...Yuri Orlov... I've heard of him. A mysterious merchant
who appears out of nowhere and sells equipment to the
Guardians...
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[2]Wow... So he's like a supporter for the Guardians?

The thing is... no one knows his true identity... but they
say all his goods are top-notch...

Oh... that communication device... It seems to be uniquely
modified, but the base is our product. Thank you for your
continued patronage.
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[2]Wow... really... He must be an amazing person...

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[11]Wait a minute! How did you get here? And where did all the
people we defeated go...?

That's a corporate secret... However, I've taken care of the
fallen guards as a service.
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[8]Taken care of them... I wonder where he put them...
There are things better left unknown.
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[8]...It seems better not to dig too deep into this.
Shall we proceed with the business then?
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[2]Even if you say business, I don't have any money right now?

No problem. My products can be exchanged for \C[2]Guardians
Points\C[0].

They are evaluation points that accumulate based on your
achievements as a Guardian. My shop supports payment with
those points under a contract with the Guardians.
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[1]Eh? So if I do well, I can exchange lots of products?

...Kohane-chan... Guardians Points are our performance
evaluation rewards, so if we use too many, our compensation
from the Guardians might decrease...

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[11]Seriously!? So in the end, it's like paying out of my own
pocket!

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[4]Mmm... I don't want my rewards to decrease, but... desperate
times call for desperate measures...

Whenever you decide whether to use our services or not,
please feel free to call on me.
Welcome. These are the products we currently have on offer.

Oh my, aren't you cold dressed like that? I recommend using
our products to restore your spiritual power and regenerate
your robe.

...I really think wandering around dressed like that is
questionable. Please regenerate your robe quickly.

Oh, what a lovely outfit. Is that the kind of play you
prefer?
We look forward to serving you again.

There are five people who have the security keys to operate
the elevator, so we need to get keys from all of them, it
seems.

It just shows how much they care about information leaks. I
wonder what the person who created this facility is
plotting...

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[4]Anyway, anyone who does terrible things to girls deserves to
be sent flying!

For that reason, first, from the \C[2]1st to 3rd
floors\C[1], there are \C[2]5 people with security
keys\C[0]. Let's collect the keys from them.

Oh, right, about that girl... The organization seems to have
strengthened their security, so it might be dangerous to
fight while protecting her. How about she waits here?

I've rewritten the security here, so it should be safe for a
while, and if it comes down to it...

Are you suggesting... that I should be the one to escort
her? Just so you know, I'm only confident in my ability to
run away.

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[8]You're confident in your ability to escape... You really are
elusive...

No, I was thinking that if it comes down to it, you could
take her and run away... Of course, I'll pay you for it at
that time.
If that's the case... I don't mind.
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[0]So with that settled, Amy-chan, will you wait here for us?
Yeah, big sister is a bit scary but... I'll wait here.
It seems there are no traps in this area.
